<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN391">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>taṇṭuḷi palapoḻin teḻili yicaikkum</l>
<l>viṇṭu vaṉaiya viṇṭōy piṟaṅkaṉ</l>
<l>mukaṭuṟa vuyarnta nelliṉ makiḻvarap</l>
<l>pakaṭutaru peruvaḷam vāḻttip peṟṟa</l>
<l>tiruntā mūri parantupaṭak keṇṭi</l>
<l>yariya lārkaiya ruṇṭiṉi tuvakkum</l>
<l>vēṅkaṭa varaippiṉ vaṭapulam pacitteṉa</l>
<l>vīṅkuvan tiṟuttaveṉ ṉirumpē rokkaṟ</l>
<l>ṟīrkai viṭukkum paṇpila mutukuṭi</l>
<l>naṉa........................................ viṉavaliṉ</l>
<l>muṉṉum vantōṉ maruṅkila ṉiṉṉu</l>
<l>maḷiya ṉākaliṟ poruna ṉivaṉeṉa</l>
<l>niṉṉuṇarn taṟiyuna reṉṉuṇarntu kūṟak</l>
<l>kāṇku vanticiṉ peruma .................</l>
<l>............. peruṅkaḻi nuḻaimī ṉaruntun</l>
<l>tutainta tūviyam putāañ cēkkun</l>
<l>tatainta puṉaṉiṉ ceḻunakar varaippi</l>
<l>ṉeñcamar kāta ṉiṉvey yōḷō</l>
<l>ṭiṉṟuyi..........................................ñcā</l>
<l>ṟuḷipata ṉaṟintu poḻiya</l>
<l>vēli yāyiram viḷaikaniṉ vayalē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Because the northern region hungers within the bounds of Vēṅkaṭam, (7)</l>
<l>where those who feed on toddy [used to] rejoice sweetly in eating (6)</l>
<l>after cutting so that they fall in a spread the imperfect pieces (5)</l>
<l>they had obtained, praising the great prosperity brought by bulls, (4)</l>
<l>while delight comes with paddy high on top (3)</l>
<l>in sky-touching heaps that are like mountains, (2)</l>
<l>when the clouds sound [in thunder] after many cool drops flew, (1)</l>
<l>the meritless old clans that released from ending (9)</l>
<l>my very big kinfolk that came here [and] camped, (8)</l>
<l>………………………… because of asking, (10)</l>
<l>as those who understand [and] know you understand [and] talk about me: (13)</l>
<l>“he who came before, he who is now without side, (11)</l>
<l>since he is pitiable. He is an artist.”,</l>
<l>I have come to see [you], o great man. ……….. (14)</l>
<l>worth of ………………….. in sweet sleep (19)</l>
<l>with her who is keen on you with love that abides in the heart, (18)</l>
<l>in the bounds of your rich mansion by the packed waves(?), (17)</l>
<l>where dense-feathered cranes dwell </l>
<l>who eat the fish that roams in the big backwaters…., (15)</l>
<l>may drop know the right time [and] flow. (20)</l>
<l>May your fields of a thousand Vēli ripen [paddy]. (21)</l>
</lg>
